to configure Apache:

1. install apache
    sudo apt-get install -y apache2
    sudo apt-get install libapache2-mod-wsgi
    sudo apt-get install libapache2-mod-wsgi python-dev

2. enable wsgi mod
    sudo a2enmod wsgi

3. sudo gedit /etc/apache2/envvars
    add this lines:
        export PRODROOT=${PRODROOT:-/home/padalko/ss_projects/Lv-164.UI/ecomap}
        export PYSRCROOT=${PYSRCROOT:-${PRODROOT}/src/python}
        export CONFROOT=${CONFROOT:-${PRODROOT}/etc}
        export PYTHONPATH=${PRODROOT}/src/python
4.  sudo gedit /etc/hosts.conf
    add:
        127.0.1.2   ecomap.new

5. sudo gedit /etc/apache2/sites-available/ecomap.conf
    #! ecomap.conf - this is config name of your site. name can be different!

    add  to that file content of apache.conf situated in this dir

6. enable your site:
    sudo a2ensite ecomap

7. ecomap.wsgi (situated in this dir):
    read comments in that file!!!
    this is your main wsgi script what apache uses to run application.
    it has already configured for our project structure
    you can set your own path to templates folder and you'll see test site

8. views.py - this is our main flask app. all code will be here. you can change everything right now.

9. PROFIT!!!!